The paper focuses on the analysis of the feature space learnt by neural networks for classification problems, specifically with the cross-entropy loss function. This falls under the domain of machine learning and deep learning, which are covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category as it covers the theoretical analysis of machine learning algorithms. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as the paper discusses the separability of classes in the feature space, which is relevant to computer vision tasks such as object recognition. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as it covers the broader field of AI, which includes machine learning. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also relevant as the paper focuses on neural networks. Finally, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the Softmax activation function, which is commonly used in natural language processing tasks.
